Educational Psychology with a concentration in Gifted & Talented Education The Master of Science in Special Education with a concentration in Gifted & Talented Education degree program is a 30 class-hour program, with an additional thesis or project in lieu of thesis. Most of this program can be taken online. >> Learn more about the MS in Special Education with a concentration in Gifted & Talented Education Master of Education in Special Education with a concentration in Autism Intervention The Master of Education in Special Education Concentration in Autism Intervention degree program is open to individuals with a four-year degree in any discipline of education (or a related field, e.g., psychology), or individuals who are currently working within a school district. >> Learn more about the MEd in Special Education with a concentration in Autism Intervention Online Programs for Secondary-Level Teacher Certification The Online Teacher Certification Program was designed for mature students who have a bachelor’s degree and want to earn initial secondary teacher certification at the graduate level. It is an 18-hour program equivalent to six courses. Of those 12 hours (4 courses) are online coursework, and the remaining 6 hours (2 courses) are either student teaching or practicum. >> Learn more about online programs for Secondary-Level Teacher Certification Back to Future Students Contact Information College of Education Matthews Hall, Room 214 1300 West Highland Street Denton, TX 76203 Contact the College of Education Email Us For technical problems with this web site, contact COEWeb@unt.edu.     UNT System UNT System UNT Dallas Campus UNT Health Science Center Universities Center at Dallas Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online Go to Secure Login Page 